{{Infobox zoo |zoo_name = Marine World Uminonakamichi |logo = |logo_caption = |logo_width = |image = |image_caption = Marine World Uminonakamichi |location = [[Higashi-ku, Fukuoka]], [[Japan]] |date_opened = April 18, 1989 |date_closed = |coordinates = {{Coord|33|39|39|N|130|21|48|E|region:JP_scale:10000|display=inline,title}} |area = {{convert|48,000|m2|ft2|abbr=on}} |num_species = 350 |num_animals = 20,000 |largest_tank_vol = {{convert|2,000|m3|gal|abbr=on}}<ref name=info>Marine World Uminonakamichi: ''[http://www.marine-world.co.jp/english/ English] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319173855/http://www.marine-world.co.jp/english/ |date=2016-03-19 }}.'' Retrieved 11 February 2015.</ref> |total_tank_vol = |annual_visitors = |members = |exhibits = |website = {{URL|http://www.marine-world.co.jp/english/index.html}} }} [[File:Megamouth shark japan.jpg|thumb|[[Megamouth shark]] specimen preserved at Marine World Uminonakamichi]]
{{nihongo|'''Marine World Uminonakamichi'''|マリンワールド海の中道|Marin-wārudō-Uminonakamichi}} is a [[public aquarium]] in [[Higashi-ku, Fukuoka]], [[Fukuoka Prefecture]], [[Japan]].
==Overview== The aquarium focuses on the aquatic life of [[Tsushima Strait|Tsushima]]'s warm current and is made up of a total of 70 tanks. The three largest contain {{convert|2,000|m3|gal|abbr=on}}, {{convert|1,400|m3|gal|abbr=on}} and {{convert|720|m3|gal|abbr=on}} respectively. The largest is used for [[dolphin]] and [[sea lion]] shows, the middle contains more than 120 [[shark]]s of 20 species, while the last is for dolphins.<ref name=info/>
Other marine mammals at the aquarium include [[sea otter]]s and [[spotted seal]]s.
==Facilities== *Marine Theater (Show Pool) A popular [[dolphin]] show is held every day at this all-weather with a seating capacity of 1,465. Visitors can enjoy watching the dolphins jump up amazingly high and go through the hoops, or the humorous performance of sea lions with the blue sea of [[Hakata Bay]] in the background.
==Access== *By train: 7-minute walk from JR [[Umi-no-Nakamichi Station]] on the [[Kashii Line]]. *By bus: 5-minute walk from Marine World Uminonakamichi bus stop. *By ferry: Take municipal ferry from Bayside Place to Uminonakamichi. Or, take Uminaka ferry line from Momochi (Marizon) to Uminonakamichi.
