'''Project 3D-VIEW''' (Virtual Interactive Environmental Worlds) is an [[educational program]] in the United States aimed at grades 5 and 6 which offers lessons in [[earth science]], [[Biology|life science]] and [[physics]] as well as general scientific principles. Lessons include seasons, [[photosynthesis]], erosion, the [[rock cycle]] and [[plate tectonics]]. It also has a study of the [[lysosphere]], the [[hydrosphere]], the [[atmosphere]] and the [[biosphere]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nasascience.nasa.gov/educators/earth-science-education-catalog/elementary-secondary-programs/project-3d-view|title=Project 3D-VIEW|work=News for Educators|publisher=NASA|accessdate=2009-03-08}}</ref> Students are immersed in a 3-dimensional representation of the topic they are studying.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.3dview.org/register_pre.cfm|title=about 3D View|publisher=U.S. Satellite Laboratory|accessdate=2009-03-08}}</ref>

The program is administrated by U.S. Satellite Laboratory, Inc., through sponsorship by [[NASA]].

