{{Culture of Burkina Faso}} '''Sport in Burkina Faso''' is widespread and includes [[association football|football]], [[basketball]], [[cycling]], [[rugby union]], [[Team handball|handball]], [[tennis]], [[athletics (sport)|athletics]], [[boxing]] and [[martial arts]].<ref name="JM">Marchais, p.102</ref><ref name="oxfam">Oxfam</ref>
==Football== {{main article|Football in Burkina Faso}} Football is very popular in Burkina Faso, played both professionally and informally in towns and villages across the country.<ref name="JM" /> The [[Burkina Faso national football team|national team]] is nicknamed "Les Etalons" ("the Stallions") in reference to the legendary horse of Princess [[Yennenga]].<ref name="JM" /> In 1998, Burkina Faso hosted the [[African Cup of Nations]] for which the [[Omnisport Stadium]] in [[Bobo-Dioulasso]] was built.<ref name="JM" /><ref>Gleeson</ref>
==Basketball== Basketball is one of the top sports in Burkina Faso for both men and women. Its [[Burkina Faso national basketball team|national team]] had its best year in 2013 when it qualified for the [[AfroBasket]], the continent's most prestigious basketball event.{{fact|date=November 2016}}
==Rugby union== {{main article|Rugby union in Burkina Faso}}Rugby union, or just rugby, in Burkina Faso is relatively new, but growing more popular every year. Rugby was introduced by the French, who had ruled Burkina Faso, or [[Republic of Upper Volta|Upper Volta]], as it was known at the time, for many years. Rugby in Burkina Faso is, like many other nations in Africa, centered around the capital, [[Ouagadougou]].{{fact|date=November 2016}}
==Cycling== Cycling is widespread both as a sport and as a cheap means of transport.<ref name="JM" /> The [[Tour du Faso]], approved by the [[Fédération internationale de cyclisme]], is a cycling event held annually in November that covers 811 miles. The [[stage race]] takes place at temperatures up to 40[[Degree (temperature)|°]][[Celsius|C]].<ref name="JM" /> It has been part of the [[UCI Africa Tour]] since 2005.{{fact|date=November 2016}}
==Olympic Games== {{main article|Burkina Faso at the Olympics}} Burkina Faso has sent athletes to every [[Summer Olympic Games]] held since 1988. Under its previous name of [[Republic of Upper Volta|Upper Volta]], the country also competed in [[1972 Summer Olympics|1972]]. Despite appearing in six different Olympics, Burkina Faso has never won an [[Olympic Games#Olympic champions and medalists|Olympic medal]]. No athletes from Burkina Faso have competed in any [[Winter Olympic Games]].{{fact|date=November 2016}}
