'''The Music Therapy Trust''' is a registered charity in [[India]] founded by [[Margaret Lobo]], who is the Founder and Director of the [[Otakar Kraus Music Trust]], UK. The trust is concerned with providing [[music therapy]] to children and adults facing difficult psycho social and physical challenges especially those from poorer section of the society. The trust is also going to establish a professional body for recognising qualified Indian music therapists named Indian Association of Professional Clinical Music Therapists (IAPCMT).

The organisation operates its administrative headquarters in India at New Delhi and in [[Kathmandu]] in Nepal.

== History ==
The idea of The Music Therapy Trust was conceived by its founder Dr. Margaret Lobo, herself a musical talent during her visit to India to give talks on music therapy in New Delhi and Mumbai. The Music Therapy Trust was established in 2005 as a registered Indian society and became the first to introduce clinical music therapy network in India.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aalatimes.com/2011/06/22/the-sound-of-music-a-healing-therapy/ |title=The sound of music – a healing therapy |publisher=AalaTimes.com |date=22 June 2011 |accessdate=2012-07-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/tabloid-news/mumbai/Music-therapy-drums-up-support/Article1-711455.aspx |title=Music therapy drums up support |work=Hindustan Times |date=20 June 2011 |accessdate=2012-07-23}}</ref>

== Activities ==
=== The Music Therapy Academy ===
TMTT launched an academy in New Delhi to train Indian musicians by offering a year-long post-graduate diploma in clinical music therapy. The course is located in the ''Action For Autism's National Centre for Autism'' in Jasola Vihar in the capital, and takes a new batch of students to train every year. It was launched by famous cricketer [[Brett Lee]], whose foundation ''MEWSIC'' is a partner in the programme.<ref name="lee">{{cite news| url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/247590/brett-lee-launches-music-therapy.html|title=Brett Lee launches music therapy school in Delhi|date=7 May 2012|accessdate=2012-06-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/tabloid-news/mumbai/Brett-Lee-to-assist-slum-children-to-keep-pace-with-musical-notes/Article1-698898.aspx|date=18 May 2011|accessdate=2012-06-24|title=Brett Lee to assist slum children to keep pace with musical notes}}</ref>
{{cquote|It is my hope to see many more of these academies across India to train Indian musicians to use their talent to transform lives of those less privileged ... Music has made a big impact on my life and so has India|author=[[Brett Lee]]|<ref name="lee" />}}

