A '''vicinal''' is a [[logology|logological]] term for a word where all its letters have "alphabetic neighbors".  For instance, if a word has an "O" in it, to be a vicinal it must also have an "N" and/or a "P".  If none of the letters have alphabetic neighbors, it is known as a nonvicinal.

